trans-unit.source: Associates an XML namespace with a document location.

The Web Services Description Language (WSDL) `import` element that is enclosed by the `definitions` element allows the separation of different parts of the XML Web service into different documents, which can then be imported as required.
Each document's URL is associated with a unique XML tag prefix that represents the XML namespace for that document's elements.
For more information about WSDL, see the specification at http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl/.
For more information about XML namespaces, see the <xref:System.Web.Services.WebServiceAttribute.Namespace%2A> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.Import"></xref> class.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionFormatExtensionCollection"></xref> associated with this <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.Import"></xref> class.
Gets or sets the value of the XML <xref uid="langword_csharp_location" name="location" href=""></xref> attribute of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_import" name="import" href=""></xref> element.
The value of the XML <xref uid="langword_csharp_location" name="location" href=""></xref> attribute of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_import" name="import" href=""></xref> element.
This value also specifies the URL of the imported document.
Gets or sets the value of the XML <xref uid="langword_csharp_namespace" name="namespace" href=""></xref> attribute of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_import" name="import" href=""></xref> element.
The value of the XML <xref uid="langword_csharp_namespace" name="namespace" href=""></xref> attribute of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_import" name="import" href=""></xref> element.

The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> of which the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.Import"></xref> is a member.
